admx-lint
------------------------------------------
admx-lint is a file verification tool, that checks ADMX/ADML contents against
their XSD schema.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.10-1
  libboost_program_options1.66-1.66.0-1
  libgcc1-14.4.0-1
  libstdc++6-14.4.0-1
  libxerces-c31-3.1.4-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.46.1-1
  cmake-4.2.1-1
  cygport-0.37.7-1
  gcc-core-14.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-14.4.0-1
  libboost-devel-1.66.0-1
  libxerces-c-devel-3.1.4-1
  ninja-1.13.2-1
  xsd-4.0.0-6

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/altlinux/admx-lint

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/altlinux/admx-lint/archive/refs/tags/0.1.0-alt1.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack admx-lint-0.1.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./admx-lint-0.1.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/admx-lint-0.1.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/admx-lint-0.1.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(admx-lint)
  /usr/bin/admx-lint.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/admx-lint.README
  /usr/share/doc/admx-lint/LICENSE.md
  /usr/share/doc/admx-lint/README.md

